#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:1
msgid "Adding a Municipality"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide is for system operators and developers onboarding a new Dutch "
"municipality to RONL Business API. Three things need to be configured: the "
"tenant configuration file, Keycloak users and groups, and (optionally) "
"municipality-specific feature flags."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:7
msgid "1. Add the tenant configuration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:9
msgid ""
"Edit `packages/frontend/public/tenants.json` and add an entry for the new "
"municipality. Use the following structure:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:11
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"tenants\": {\n"
"    \"newtown\": {\n"
"      \"id\": \"newtown\",\n"
"      \"name\": \"newtown\",\n"
"      \"displayName\": \"Gemeente Nieuwstad\",\n"
"      \"municipalityCode\": \"0999\",\n"
"      \"theme\": {\n"
"        \"primary\": \"#2E4057\",\n"
"        \"primaryDark\": \"#1A2A3A\",\n"
"        \"primaryLight\": \"#6B8CAD\",\n"
"        \"secondary\": \"#F4A261\",\n"
"        \"accent\": \"#E76F51\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"features\": {\n"
"        \"zorgtoeslag\": true,\n"
"        \"kinderbijslag\": false,\n"
"        \"huurtoeslag\": false,\n"
"        \"processes\": [\"zorgtoeslag\"]\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"contact\": {\n"
"        \"phone\": \"14 0999\",\n"
"        \"email\": \"info@nieuwstad.nl\",\n"
"        \"address\": \"Stadhuis 1\",\n"
"        \"postalCode\": \"1234 AB\",\n"
"        \"city\": \"Nieuwstad\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      \"enabled\": true\n"
"    }\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:45
msgid ""
"The `id` value must match the `municipality` claim that Keycloak will issue "
"in the JWT for users of this municipality (see step 2 below)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:47
msgid ""
"Theme colours follow the municipality's visual identity. The `primary` "
"colour is applied to buttons, headers, and active navigation items. Use "
"sufficient contrast against white text (WCAG AA minimum)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:51
msgid "2. Configure Keycloak"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:53
msgid ""
"Open the Keycloak Admin Console (ACC: `https://acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl/"
"admin`, PROD: `https://keycloak.open-regels.nl/admin`), realm `ronl`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:55
msgid "**Create roles:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:57
msgid "Under **Realm roles**, add:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:58
msgid "`citizen-newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:59
msgid "`caseworker-newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:61
msgid ""
"Or, if using the municipality-prefixed role convention that the JWT "
"middleware already supports, simply add the generic `citizen` and "
"`caseworker` roles to new user accounts with an attribute `municipality = "
"newtown`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:63
msgid "**Add the municipality attribute mapper:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:65
msgid ""
"The `municipality` claim in the JWT is populated by a Keycloak protocol "
"mapper on the `ronl-business-api` client. Verify the mapper named "
"`municipality` exists under:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:67
msgid ""
"Clients → ronl-business-api → Client scopes\n"
"  → ronl-business-api-dedicated → Mappers → municipality"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:72
msgid ""
"The mapper reads the `municipality` user attribute and injects it into the "
"access token. Set `municipality = newtown` on each user account belonging to "
"the new municipality."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:74
msgid "**Create test users:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:76
msgid "Under **Users**, create:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "Username"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "Role"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "`test-citizen-newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\user-guide\\adding-municipality.md:78"
msgid "`municipality = newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "`citizen`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "`test-caseworker-newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:78
msgid "`caseworker`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:83
msgid ""
"Set a temporary password and mark it as non-temporary for test accounts."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:87
msgid "3. Add backend tenant middleware allowlist"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:89
msgid ""
"If `ENABLE_TENANT_ISOLATION=true` in the backend `.env`, verify that "
"`newtown` is included in the allowed tenants list in `packages/backend/src/"
"middleware/tenant.middleware.ts`. If the middleware uses a hard-coded list, "
"add the new municipality ID."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:93
msgid "4. Deploy and verify"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:95
msgid "After making these changes:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:97
msgid ""
"Rebuild and redeploy the frontend (the `tenants.json` change requires a new "
"static build)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:98
msgid ""
"No backend restart is required if tenant isolation is configured via "
"environment variables"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:99
msgid "Log in using `test-citizen-newtown` / `test123` on the portal"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:100
msgid "Verify the correct municipality theme and display name appear"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:101
msgid "Verify that `GET /v1/health` still returns `healthy`"
msgstr ""
